<subSubSection pageId="8" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,602,1614,1640]" box="[151,602,1614,1640]" pageId="8">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,602,1614,1640]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="8" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,602,1614,1640]" pageId="8">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Elwes" authorityYear="1890" box="[151,424,1614,1640]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Barsura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simplicifascia">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,424,1614,1640]" italics="true" pageId="8">Barsura simplicifascia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,1685,2034]" pageId="8">
The male genitalia of the species-group are characterized in the medially broader valva with a broad trigonal distal costal process with an arcuated dorsal margin (whereas in the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Walker" authorityYear="1864" box="[850,999,1721,1745]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Asura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nubifascia">
<emphasis box="[850,999,1721,1745]" italics="true" pageId="8">B. nubifascia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group the distal costal process is narrow and trapezoidal), presence of a short trigonal ampulla with a broad base in the medial part of costa (in the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Walker" authorityYear="1864" box="[151,299,1793,1817]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Asura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nubifascia">
<emphasis box="[151,299,1793,1817]" italics="true" pageId="8">B. nubifascia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group only 
<taxonomicName authority="Volynkin &amp; Dubatolov &amp; Kishida, 2017" authorityName="Volynkin &amp; Dubatolov &amp; Kishida" authorityYear="2017" box="[527,686,1794,1817]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Barsura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="contrastata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[527,686,1794,1817]" italics="true" pageId="8">B. contrastata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[693,783,1793,1818]" pageId="8" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[693,783,1793,1818]" pageId="8">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
has an ampulla, but it is pimple-like), the relatively small cornuti in the apical field (whereas in the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Walker" authorityYear="1864" box="[614,762,1829,1853]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Asura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nubifascia">
<emphasis box="[614,762,1829,1853]" italics="true" pageId="8">B. nubifascia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group the upper cornuti are large), the cornuti in the lateral field having about the same size (whereas in the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Walker" authorityYear="1864" box="[770,918,1865,1889]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Asura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nubifascia">
<emphasis box="[770,918,1865,1889]" italics="true" pageId="8">B. nubifascia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group the cornuti have different size), and presence of an additional apico-lateral diverticulum with a field of short spine-like cornuti; in the female genitalia, the antevaginal plate is narrow, weakly sclerotized, not wrinkly, whereas in the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Walker" authorityYear="1864" box="[1186,1337,1937,1961]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Asura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nubifascia">
<emphasis box="[1186,1337,1937,1961]" italics="true" pageId="8">B. nubifascia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
speciesgroup the antevaginal plate is large, wrinkly sclerotized, with deep round concave near its conjunction with ostium bursae.
</paragraph>
